XCIV. This epigram is generally interpreted to mean that Hippocrates sent Martial a present of mulsum, made with Sardinian honey, asking for a present of mulsum, that is properly made mulsum, in return. But judging from the name Hippocrates, evidently a fictitious one, it seems more natural to suppose that Martial is speaking of a doctor, who sent him a draught, and asked him for 'mulsum in payment, a request which Martial affects to treat with comic indignation.
